SensorDataListener - Class in at.ac.tuwien.ict.andropicar.rmcs.connection
This class is being used by the RMCSs interfaces to know what DistanceSensorData should be forwarded to what ISensorDataListener.
It is essentially a Tuple, with one attribute being the ISensorDataListener that wants to receive updates about sensor-events and the other being a list of EDataTypes that should be forwarded to the listener.
Equality between two instances of this class, is determined by SensorDataListener.listener.

ServerConnection - Class in at.ac.tuwien.ict.andropicar.rmcs.network
This class is used to communicate with a TCP-Server via a TCP-connection and is able to send sensor-data to the server and receive control-data from the server to control the car.
Listeners are able to register themselves with the ServerConnection to get updated about sending and receiving data as well as connection updates.

STM32SpiInterface - Class in at.ac.tuwien.ict.andropicar.rmcs.stm32
An Interface to control the data transmission to a STM32, that is connected through SPI.

Used Pins for SPI communication:
- MOSI _ GPIO12 _ Pin 19
- MISO _ GPIO13 _ Pin 21
- SCK __ GPIO14 _ Pin 23
- GND __ ______ _ Pin 25
- GND __ ______ _ Pin 6
- TxD __ GPIO15 _ Pin 8
- RxD __ GPIO16 _ Pin 10

for pinout see: Raspberry Pi Pinout DON'T FORGET TO ENABLE SPI INTERFACE IN RASPI-CONFIG!
